column1: Supplementary Table S1: List of all the phosphopeptides detected in at least 2 out of 3 donors and correspondingly quantified.
Unique phosphopeptides were summarized from the raw MS data. All Phosphopeptides detected in at least 2 of 3 donors were considered for quantitative analysis.

Quantile normalization was performed on dimethyl signal intensities, then intensity values were log2-transformed and missing values were imputed using nearest neighbor averaging . A linear model was fit in limma with the group and the donor as factors in the design matrix. P values from Empirical Bayes moderated t test are given.

Phosphopeptides with respective phosphosites and corresponding sequences, protein accession numbers and gene names are presented as individual donors' as well as averaged log2 ratio. NAs indicate peptides not detected in the respective donor
